.TH "usb_alloc_streams" 9 "usb_alloc_streams" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
usb_alloc_streams \- allocate bulk endpoint stream IDs.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" usb_alloc_streams
.BI "(struct usb_interface *interface "  ","
.BI "struct usb_host_endpoint **eps "  ","
.BI "unsigned int num_eps "  ","
.BI "unsigned int num_streams "  ","
.BI "gfp_t mem_flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "interface" 12
alternate setting that includes all endpoints.
.IP "eps" 12
array of endpoints that need streams.
.IP "num_eps" 12
number of endpoints in the array.
.IP "num_streams" 12
number of streams to allocate.
.IP "mem_flags" 12
flags hcd should use to allocate memory.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Sets up a group of bulk endpoints to have \fInum_streams\fP stream IDs available.
Drivers may queue multiple transfers to different stream IDs, which may
complete in a different order than they were queued.
.SH "RETURN"
On success, the number of allocated streams. On failure, a negative
error code.
